<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Diplomat-Shoplifter     09-09 0185</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Diplomat-Shoplifter,0190</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>RETRANSMITTING a0880 to fix numbering</HEAD>
<HEAD>Egyptian Official Fined for Shoplifting</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Egyptian government official was fined 750
pounds ($1,275) for shoplifting at the Selfridges department store
in London.
   Soraya Abdulla, first undersecretary of state for education,
pleaded innocent and said she accidentally walked out of the store
while looking for a cashier to accept payment for goods she had
chosen.
   She was arrested Aug. 29 after walking out of the store on
Oxford Street in London's West End carrying four ties, a brooch and
four pairs of earrings worth about $370 in all.
   Mrs. Abdulla, visiting Britain as guest of the British Council,
a government-funded cultural organization, had currency worth
$2,665 in her purse when she was arrested, Constable Nick Farmer
told the court.
   He said she told him: ``I didn't mean to steal. I didn't know I
was leaving the store. I really meant to pay. I was in a hurry and
forgot.''
   Passing judgment Thursday, magistrate Roger Davies said: ``The
West End stores are plagued by foreign visitors who come here and
abuse our hospitality by stealing.''
</TEXT>
