<HEAD>Three Sue To Have `Last Temptation' Name Changed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three people have sued to change the title of
``The Last Temptation of Christ'' to ``The Lies and Profanations of
Universal Pictures as pertaining to the life of Our Lord and
Savior, Jesus Christ.''
   The three Pittsburgh residents said in an Allegheny County
Common Pleas lawsuit filed recently that the controversial film
turns Jesus Christ into a ``vacillating, weak, sinful and almost
demented individual.''
