<HEAD>Flooding Possible in Florida; Florence Changing Slightly in
Strength</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Rain this morning threatened possible flooding in central and
northern Florida, and tropical storm Florence changed just slightly
in strength as it drifted slowly 365 miles south of New Orleans.
   Rain extended across Georgia and parts of the Carolinas, and
early morning skies were cloudy over the central Atlantic states
and the upper Mississippi Valley.
   The rest of the nation was partly cloudy or clear.
   Florence drifted northward at about 5 mph, and was expected to
continue in that direction about 12 hours.
   The tropical storm's highest sustained winds were about 55 mph
with gusts to near hurricane force in squalls.
   Today's national weather forecast called for showers and
thunderstorms extending from eastern Virginia across the Carolinas
to central Florida; Georgia, Alabama and eastern Mississippi.
   High temperatures were forecast in the 60s in upper Michigan and
the northern Pacific Coast; the 70s from the rest of Washington
state across northern Montana, North Dakota, Minnesota, the Great
Lakes, the northern Appalachians and from New England across New
Jersey; and near 90 and in the 90s in the southern Plains, and from
the Great Basin across southern Oregon. Highs in the desert
Southwest likely will reach near 110 degrees.
   The rest of the nation should be in the 80s.
   The nation's temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 37 degrees
at Yellowstone, Wyo., to 91 at Blythe, Calif.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 63 rain; Boston 58 fair; Buffalo 59 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 69 rain; Cincinnati 58 fair; Cleveland 61 partly
cloudy; Detroit 62 fair; Miami 82 partly cloudy; New York 65
cloudy; Philadelphia 67 cloudy; Pittsburgh 51 fair; Portland, Maine
54 fair; Washington 65 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 44 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 73 fair; Denver 67
hazy; Des Moines 57 partly cloudy; Indianapolis 61 foggy; Kansas
City 67 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 51 fair; Nashville 59 fair; New
Orleans 71 fair; St. Louis 68 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 76 windy; Anchorage 45 fair; Las Vegas 83
fair; Los Angeles 64 cloudy; Phoenix 88 fair; Salt Lake City 60
fair; San Diego 68 cloudy; San Francisco 59 fair; Seattle 57 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 61 fair; Toronto 61 fair.
