<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Cocoa Death,0127</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Dies After Fall Into Cocoa Vat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ELOISE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man mixing ice cream flavoring died after
falling into a vat of cocoa powder, authorities said.
   Jim Bill Young, 20, may have inhaled the cocoa dust in the
45-inch-deep vat and suffocated, said Polk County sheriff's
spokeswoman Lynne Breidenbach.
   Young was standing on a 7{-foot platform, dumping 25-pound bags
of cocoa into a vat Thursday at the Imperiral Flavors plant, when
he fell, Breidenbach said. ``We don't know if he lost his balance
or what,'' she said.
   Young's brother, who also works at the plant, saw him fall and
sought help.
   Rescuers removed some of the powder and pulled Young free, but
he died at the scene.
