   Oldsmobile is aiming its 1989 model
lineup at buyers younger than those traditionally associated with
the General Motors division's cars.
   ``We think our products are ahead of our image,'' Warren
Christell, Oldsmobile's general manager for marketing, said
Thursday. ``We haven't done a good job of telling people about it.''
   Oldsmobile executives showed off an advertising campaign for the
1989 cars that features children and grandchildren of famous people.
