<DATELINE>SEATTLE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Boeing Co. announced orders for five 767
passenger jets for at least $421 million on Thursday, boosting the
company's total jetliner orders for the year to more than $21
billion.
   Statements issued by Boeing said four 767-300 extended-range
aircraft were ordered by Gulf Air, the national carrier of Bahrain,
Oman, Qatar and the United Arab Emirates, for delivery in April,
May and June.
