<HEAD>London Share Prices Rally At Midday</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Will be led after the closing</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices drifted slightly higher around midday
Friday, after recovering from sharply lower levels near the opening.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was up 2.8
points, or 0.2 percent, at 1,742.6 at about 12:45 p.m. local time,
just 0.1 percent below its best level of the day.
   The index dropped as much as 22.1 points in early trading.
   Dealers said they were puzzled by the sudden surge in prices.
Buyers poured in, afraid of missing out on the market's recovery,
and market makers chased prices higher, dealers said.
   ``We are seeing quite a bit of buying at lower levels,'' said
one dealer.
   Volume was better than it has been for several days, with 239.6
million shares changing hands by midday, compared with 226.8
million shares at the same time Thursday.
