<2ND_LINE>BC-EEC-Unemployment,0107</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>EEC July Jobless Rate Unchanged At 10.4 Percent From June</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The unemployment rate in the European
Economic Community stood at 10.4 percent in July, unchanged from
June but slightly higher than a year ago, a report released Friday
said.
   Eurostat, the EEC statistics agency, said 15.6 million people
were listed as unemployed in the 12-nation trading bloc during July.
   The EEC jobless rate was 10.6 percent in July 1987.
   Eurostat said unemployment in Britain, Spain and Portugal has
been falling steadily for over a year while Italy and Denmark
posted increases over the same period.
