<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Ford-Nissan     09-09 0174</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Ford-Nissan,0182</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Governor's Schedule Confirms Ford-Nissan Ohio Joint Venture</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. and the Japanese automaker
Nissan were expected to announce plans next week for a joint
venture that would manufacture minivans at a yet-to-be-built Ohio
plant.
   Ohio Gov. Richard Celeste, who will be in Japan from Sunday
through Thursday, has scheduled a news conference with Ford and
Nissan officials in Tokyo Monday to announce the venture, according
to an itinerary released by Celeste's office Thursday.
   Ford and Nissan officials have yet to confirm plans for the
joint venture.
   Ford reportedly has considered plans to build a factory next to
its Ohio Truck Plant in Avon Lake, according to a proposal Ford
officials submitted to Lorain County communities last week.
   Ford executives reportedly were to discuss the project during a
board of directors meeting Thursday in Detroit, but Ford spokesman
John Spelich would not confirm whether the venture was in fact on
the agenda.
   Asked whether Ford planned to make any announcements Monday,
Spelich said only, ``That's a possibility.''
</TEXT>
